job_description_lines:
Title:     Quality Assurance Data Analyst  
 Location: Remote 
 Duration: 1+year 

  Job Description:   
  Top 3 Required Skills: detail-oriented with a focus on DATA, SQL some experience, prefers remote work experience with constant team coordination, Excellent verbal and written communication skills  
  Onsite/Remote; indefinitely: Remote  
  Time Zone Requirements: PST, unless candidates are willing to work 10 am - 7 pm PST  
  Work Schedule: 10 am - 7 pm PST (training hours will be 8 am - 5 pm PST)  
  Interview Process: 1st Interview - virtual/webcam w/Manager and possibly one other member of the team; 2nd interview will be virtual/webcam, and likely panel (at least two on our end) and will include a tech assessment.  
  Potential for Conversion to FTE (salary range): Yes  
  Potential for Extension: No  
  Spotlight Call: TBD  

  Roles and Responsibilities in Quality Assurance  
  Job responsibilities require that the QA Data Analyst meet the critical job demands, including but not limited to, the following key areas: 
  Confirm the accuracy of various data updates and extracts, which involves understanding the logic of complex queries, stored procedures, triggers, and functions based on requirements, writing appropriate test queries, and executing them to verify the logic and data 
  Work closely with data engineers, business analysts, and other QA team members to identify, report, and troubleshoot defects; verify problem fixes in a detailed, efficient, and timely manner 

  Job Qualifications and Requirements  
  Excellent verbal and written communication skills; Excellent analytical and organizational skills; Strong deductive reasoning 
  Ability to multi-task and work separate projects in a fast paced & dynamic company environment and extremely tight timelines 
  Demonstrated ability to work independently with limited direction or as part of a team 
  T-SQL to include understanding of the following concepts: 
  Aggregates: COUNT, SUM, MAX/MIN, DISTINCT, GROUP BY, HAVING 
  JOINs, ANSI-89 and 
  ANSI-92 syntax. 
  UNION vs UNION ALL 

  Work Environment  
  Work is fast-paced and performed in an office environment, or remote-office environment with regular use of webcam and screen-sharing, and with extensive contact with employees, and occasional contact with clients. The industry we serve demands the highest level of confidentiality and professionalism in safeguarding client and project information. Highly effective Class Action & Claims Solutions and Corporate Services associates thrive on being in an environment that rewards the following critical success factors: 
  Adaptability: Appropriately responding to changing situations without a loss of effectiveness and enthusiasm for strategic initiatives and corporate goals. 
  Analysis: Identifying problems and causes or analyzing how processes and procedures could be improved, collecting relevant information and identifying possible solutions. 
  Attention to Detail: Appropriately completing all of the individual tasks accurately or according to workflow/process guidelines with an emphasis on reaching or exceeding quality standards. 
  Creativity: Being inventive, imaginative, and innovative. 
  Energy: Maintaining a fast, active pace in the normal course of a day. 
  Flexibility: Going into situations without preconceived notions, but with a willingness to assess various options, in order to determine a course of action. 
  Integrity: Strict adherence to job-related standards, values or norms. 
  Learning Ability: Understanding and applying new information. 
  Listening: Hearing and comprehending verbal messages and confirming back what is heard. 
  Team Player: Functioning as an active member of a group while maintaining focus on ones individual contributions and responsibilities. 
  Verbal & Written Communication: Effective oral, written, and nonverbal expression without preparation. 

  Physical Demands  
  The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essentials functions. 
  Position requires no significant manual labor. 
  Position does require moderate standing, sitting, carrying and walking. 
  Position requires infrequent lifting, repetitive bending and/or moving. 
  Position requires close vision, distant vision, peripheral vision, and depth perception. 
  Position requires talking and listening to communications with clients and employees.

The Varsity Tutors platform has thousands of students looking for online Data Analysis tutors nationally and in Virginia Beach. As a tutor who uses the Varsity Tutors platform, you can earn good money, choose your own hours, and truly make a difference in the lives of your students.

Enjoy competitive rates and get paid 2x per week.Choose to tutor as much or as little as you want.Set your own hours and schedule.Get paired with students best-suited to your teaching style and preferences (from thousands of potential clients).Tutor online (i.e. “work remotely”) using our purpose-built Live Learning Platform.Students can take adaptive assessments through the platform and share results to help you decide where to focus.We collect payment from the customers, so all you have to do is invoice the session.

About Varsity Tutors And 1-on-1 Online Tutoring

Our mission is to transform the way people learn. We do this by leveraging advanced technology, AI, and the latest in learning science to facilitate a personalized learning experience. With 1-on-1 Online Tutoring, individual students are connected with tutors for a highly personalized learning experience. We believe our thoughtful approach to matching students with the right tutors can improve outcomes, and we look forward to connecting you with students hungry to learn.

Job Description

GDIT is seeking an experienced Data Analyst to work in a dynamic agile team environment. The Data Analyst will be part of a technically diverse Support team supporting Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) via the Integrated Data Repository (IDR) contract. The Integrated Data Repository (IDR) is a high-volume data warehouse integrating Parts A, B, C, D, and DME claims, beneficiary and provider data sources, along with ancillary data such as contract information, risk scores, and many others. Access to this robust integrated data supports a variety of strategic analytics across CMS. It’s this team’s vision/goal to support these analytics at CMS through:
Continuous and improved information sharing with CMS Stakeholders and IDR usersSimplified User Onboarding and system access processesEnhancing data quality and integration with other systemsStrengthening query and analytic capabilities through constant and iterative enhancementsProactive evaluation and testing of tools/services to better support Analytical use cases
Responsibilities

As a member of the Support team (an Agile Kanban team) the Data Analyst will be responsible for activities (including but not limited to):
Triaging user reported issuesAssisting users with data analysis at varying levels of complexity/use casesAddressing data questions and/or data discrepanciesDebugging user queries and proactively identifying areas for improvements/enhancementsCollaborating with other business subject matter and technical experts to resolve user questions/issuesIdentifying process improvements and opportunities for automation
Required Skills
Bachelor's Degree and 5 Years of relevant experienceExtensive SQL experienceFundamental Architectural Knowledge of SnowflakeProficiency with utilizing Snowflake to analyze dataProficiency using Atlassian tools (Confluence, Jira) for task tracking and project documentationFamiliarity with healthcare claims dataPrior experience supporting Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS)
Preferred Skills
Fundamental Architectural Knowledge of TeradataFundamental Architectural Knowledge of DatabricksComfortable developing how-to and other user facing documentation to support the system user baseWillingness to explore new tools, analyze new data, and in general want to continue expanding skill sets

Help Us Shape the Future of Healthcare

At League, we’re big on building connections - both through our product and with each other. Our platform is consumer centric, personalized and always on. We’re reimagining the health benefits experience to give people a more consumer-centric way to manage their health: immediate, seamless, and tailored to their unique needs. It’s a front door to healthcare that empowers people to live healthier, happier lives. Every day.

As a Data Analyst, you will help us create an engaging product that improves the health outcomes of our users. In this role, you will use in-depth analysis and governance of business intelligence, to enable and drive our product managers and marketing team to improve the user experience and engagement on our platform.

People who have worked within cross-functional and multi-disciplined teams (and enjoyed doing so) will thrive in this role. Furthermore, you have experience in tying numbers to a larger, more strategic, business context. You enjoy communicating with non-technical stakeholders, using the art of converting simple questions into complex analysis and translating them back into meaningful and actionable insights.

Our data team also manages an internal Business Intelligence product that primarily leverages a SQL-based ETL to surface key performance indicators company-wide within Looker. You will be working closely with data engineers and data scientists on the team to build and maintain our data pipelines to ingest and transform data from a variety of sources to support these BI tools.

In This Role, You Will
 Develop analytics strategies and frameworks to monitor and analyze product performance and business KPIs related to application usage, and user engagement & conversion.  Provide insights through analysis to help inform decisions in all parts of the business, including Product Management, Marketing, and Healthcare.  Work closely with internal stakeholders to define the work you take on in support of their teams, as well as communicate data considerations and issues they need to consider in their work.  Work closely with data-engineers and data-scientists on data requirements, reporting and forecasting of metrics.  Regularly conduct tagging audits and analysis to ensure the accuracy of reports, in particular of the client events generated by user button clicks and screen loads within the app. 
Attributes
 You care deeply about using information and data in decision-making and have experience in communicating that logic to stakeholders.  You are a strong problem solver and can communicate the challenges and solutions effectively  You are a strong communicator and comfortable collaborating with groups and at times, training or educating teams to use data tools or to understand results  You drive to learn and master new technologies and techniques.  You like working in a fast-paced environment and are comfortable managing multiple tasks to tight deadlines.  You are eager to learn from others and help others grow with you. 
Desired Outcome
 Ownership of stakeholder relationship, where your consistent and impactful analysis and business intelligence work is aligned with company objectives.  Empower your stakeholders to make data driven decisions by guiding and assisting them to use our data products and by providing them with data insights. 
Required Education/Experience/Certificates
 Strong SQL skills and experience working with a modern ETL framework  Experience working as a data analyst or data scientist  Undergraduate or Masters degree in business administration, statistics, computer science or similarly quantitative discipline, or equivalent practical experience 
Nice To Have Experience
Data analysis and data manipulation in Python (Pandas, PySpark, etc)Healthcare industry experience

You are the driving force behind our company.

Start your career with Ryder today!

Summary

The Data Analyst role is to deliver a final business solution to the operations team through a Power Bi experience. The Data Analyst's technical skills will be put to the test as they shape data into a crispy design through a smooth user experience. Over time the Data Analyst will become a domain expert of supply chains and their use cases. This position will work on cutting edge data technology as a key user on Ryder's Azure Data Lake driving the analytics initiatives. Design critical analytical dashboards, reports and queries to drive strategic business decisions, ad-hoc analysis and identify descriptive and prescriptive solutions for internal Ryder teams and external customers. Dig deep into the core issues of business problems in order to drive a solution that gets at the heart of the causative problem. On this team, the Data Analyst will get the chance to be the expert of supply chain solutions, collaborating with Data Analysts and Scientists, using all the skills in order to exploit data to drive the business forward. This will push the envelope of what is possible within the big data space; streaming live data into a data lake and experimenting with data in the data sandbox.

Essential Functions
Develop Dashboards by understanding business needs, interpret the integrated data and translate this into usable visualizations to drive business decisions, interpreting results and how to utilize the dashboardsEngage the business, evaluating their needs and ad-hoc requests to prioritize product efforts creating new innovative solutionsKnowledge of the Ryder Business, understanding the complexity of the supply chain world and the role that data has within this ecosystemEnhance data maturity and integration to standardize the core value add functionality enabling a multiplier effect
Additional Responsibilities
Performs other duties as assigned.
Skills And Abilities
Experience developing BI solutions with tools like: Power BI TableauExposure using tools like: ETL tools (Alteryx or SSIS) Data manipulation tools (SQL) Object oriented development stacks (.net) (preferred)Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to express complex technical concepts in business termsSupport product innovation, working closely with technology throughout the build, test, and release of the product using agile methodologies
Qualifications
Bachelor's degree required Supply Chain, Data Analytics or equivalentMaster's degree preferred Supply Chain, Data Analytics, MBA or equivalentTwo (2) years or more Applied Project(s) Experience: Experience in demonstrating, digital transformation, data management in an educational/project or intern type environment requiredTwo (2) years or more 2-4 years experience in creating dashboards for diagnostic analysis across the business. Experience working in a cloud environment a plus. preferred
DOT Regulated: No

Job Category: Data Science & Analytics

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, status as a protected veteran, among other things, or status as a qualified individual with disability.

Job Description

 American Homes 4 Rent 

As one of the country’s fastest-growing property management companies of single-family rental homes, American Homes 4 Rent has an exhilarating and fluid start-up culture and permanency of a well-founded corporation, rich with diversity. As pioneers in the industry, solidified by our place on Wall Street, American Homes 4 Rent (NYSE: AMH) is currently looking for qualified candidates. With a culture of unprecedented growth, quality and innovative collaboration, we are seeking personalities to complement our attributes.

The Data Analyst designs and maintains data systems and databases by troubleshooting coding errors and other data-related problems. Mines data from primary and secondary sources, translates data into a readable format. Analyzes and evaluates data, provides explanations, reports, and visualizations to show insights determined from the data to senior leaders and collaborating departments. Identifies new sources of data and methods to improve data collection, analysis, and reporting to describe the current state of reality for the organization by translating data into information accessible to the business. Utilizes statistical tools to interpret data sets and analyzes trends and patterns that are valuable for diagnostic and predictive analysis. Works independently with general supervision. Problems faced are difficult but typically not complex. Influence others within the job area through explanation of facts, policies, and practices. (This is a remote role)

 Responsibilities: 
 Extracts data from primary and secondary sources and assess the quality and meaning of data, translates data into a readable format. Uses statistical tools to identify, analyze, and interpret patterns and trends in complex data sets that could be helpful for diagnosis and prediction.  Collaborates with ETL developers, business intelligence developers, data scientists, and senior leaders to identify process improvement opportunities, proposes system modifications, and devises data governance strategies to incorporate best practices and policies.  Performs exploratory data analysis and scrutinizes data to recognize and identify patterns. Uses data modeling techniques to create summaries and key observations for functional service lines e.g., Data Architecture, Data Governance, Business Intelligence, and Data Science.  Collaborates with the Data Science team for sourcing external data and ingesting into the Data Science development environment. Maintains the Data Science database instance and all datasets that have been scoped for analysis.  Develops and leads multiple cross-departmental projects and establishes effective working relationships with assigned client groups to deliver business results. Engages with cross functional teams on integration efforts for merging data platforms with enterprise systems and applications. 

 Requirements: 
 High School Diploma/GED required.  Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, Finance, Management Information Systems, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, Statistics, Economics, and/or related field preferred.  Minimum 3 years in Data Analytics/Reporting, Information Management Systems, Business intelligence tools, and/or related.  Advanced experience and knowledge of Excel, data visualizations, analytics.  Intermediate experience and knowledge of SQL programming.  Intermediate experience and knowledge of ETL framework and ETL tools including Microsoft SSIS.  Intermediate experience and knowledge business intelligence tools (Power BI, SSRS, SSAS, Tableau). 

 Work where you feel right at home – 

If you are a versatile professional who values culture, a concerted environment and the potential for exponential growth, we want to work with you! Apply now and someone from our Talent Acquisition team will reach out to you soon!

For positions that are permitted or required to work remotely, employees may conduct work only within the United States and only in states where the Company is already conducting business, unless for brief periods, consistent with Company policy.

For employees in Colorado only, the anticipated range is $67,050 to $95,865. Actual starting base salary will depend on geographical location, skills, and relevant experience.

The Company also may provide benefits with this position including but not limited to: medical, dental, and vision insurance; Flexible Spending Accounts (FSUs) and/or Health Savings Accounts (HSAs); Dependent Savings Accounts; 401(k) plan with employer matching; employee stock purchase plan; and potential for bonuses. The above wage range is the Company’s current good faith expectation for this position. The actual amount paid and/or offered may be less or more than this range and will be based on factors including geographic location, education, training, or experience related to the work, seniority, merit, quantity and or quality of the work.

Information regarding AH4R’s collection and use of your personal information can be found at https://www.ah4r.com/employeeprivacy

 Related Keywords: 

Data Analysis, Coding, Information Technology, Business Intelligence, Analytics, Collaborative, Reporting, Troubleshoot, Analyst

job_description_lines:
Overview

Frontdoor is a company that’s obsessed with taking the hassle out of owning a home. With services powered by people and enabled by technology, it is the parent company of four home service plan brands: American Home Shield, HSA, Landmark and OneGuard, as well as ProConnect, an on-demand membership service for home repairs and maintenance, and Streem, a technology company that enables businesses to serve customers through an enhanced augmented reality, computer vision and machine learning platform. Frontdoor serves 2.2 million customers across the U.S. through a network of approximately 17,000 pre-qualified contractor firms that employ an estimated 60,000 technicians. The company’s customizable home service plans help customers protect and maintain their homes from costly and unexpected breakdowns of essential home systems and appliances. With 50 years of home services experience, the company responds to over four million service requests annually. For details, visit frontdoorhome.com.

Responsibilities

Responsible for providing data analysis to recommend actions of a moderately complex nature to improve business processes to management.
Gather, validate, and analyze data, to successfully manage internal performance reporting and messaging for OperationsAnalyze lost productivity within our BPO vendors and estimate budgetary impactsCompile and analyze interval call volume data and lost productivity risks and make short term schedule recommendations to create operational efficienciesOwn agent performance scorecards, published monthly, to assist management with performance managementTrack overtime from a productive and budgetary perspective and forecast expected monthly expense and requirementsPresent weekly staffing changes and assist in determining staffing needs to meet operational goalsAssist with labor requirement forecasting and make recommendations on the timing of staff additions based on historical behaviorsPerform frequent ad hoc reporting on demand to assist Operations management with decision making
Qualifications
3 years overall data analysis experience with proven experience in SQL, R, PowerBI, Looker or other data management/visualization tools.Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, or similar field.Ability to mine data, compile and manipulate in multiple systems/programs and analyze resultsSQL (Snowflake)RLookerPowerBIPythonAbility to create effective presentations for management.Excellent communication skills

We can recommend jobs specifically for you!

Type Full Time

job_description_lines:
Description

UPMC Health Plan and WorkPartners is looking for an Integrated Data Analyst to produce in-depth reporting and analytics for employer group clients, internal business line leaders and executive management. The analyst will help identify and monitor health and absence risks in populations and evaluate the impact of implementing integrated health and productivity solutions. As a support for business line leaders, analyst will demonstrate the ability to deconstruct existing business processes and make specific recommendations for operational improvements. The position has potential for exceptional career growth opportunities.

This role is REMOTE! Apply today!

Responsibilities
Apply data-mining, statistical and advanced modeling techniques.Meet deadlines and turnaround times set by managers and department director (these deadlines and turnaround times will, at times, require the employee to work until the project is completed, meaning extended daily work hours, extended work weeks, or both).Compare performance against regional, national and international benchmarks.Document requirements and define project scope and objectives under the direction of senior-level Analysts.Demonstrate consistent application of strong problem-solving skills in the creation and interpretation of quantitative analyses, and to assist in development of analysis plans.Demonstrate business acumen and knowledge of data elements for multiple product lines.Design, construct and summarize in-depth analyses.Create and maintain operational and customer-facing reports supporting UPMC Health Plan and WorkPartners products.Complete tasks with an emphasis on quality and accuracy.Explain findings to both technical and non-technical audiences, including customers and senior management.Regularly collaborate with team members and see projects through to completion.Train new and existing staff on current and new products, processes and techniques.
Qualifications Bachelor's degree in analytics, economics, mathematics, computer science, statistics or a related field required. Equivalent work experience will be considered.Master's degree preferred. 2 years of experience in data analytics required.Strong computer skills required, with knowledge in database-management systems such as Oracle or Microsoft SQL Server required.Data manipulation and visualization (experience with Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint is very useful; Power BI)Data procurement and manipulation (experience coding/querying [especially SQL and/or SAS] would be extremely helpful)High degree of professionalism, enthusiasm, autonomy and initiativeAbility to work in a fast-paced environment.Ability to manage multiple tasks and projects, and forge strong interpersonal relationships within the department, with other departments, and with external audiences.Attention to detail is critical to the success of this position. Interpret and communicate to management and colleagues, verbally and through written reports, the results of complex, quantitative analysis.
Licensure, Certifications, And Clearances

UPMC is an Equal Opportunity Employer/Disability/Veteran

Total Rewards

More than just competitive pay and benefits, UPMC’s Total Rewards package cares for you in all areas of life — because we believe that you’re at your best when receiving the support you need: professional, personal, financial, and more.

Our Values

At UPMC, we’re driven by shared values that guide our work and keep us accountable to one another. Our Values of Quality & Safety, Dignity & Respect, Caring & Listening, Responsibility & Integrity, Excellence & Innovation play a vital role in creating a cohesive, positive experience for our employees, patients, health plan members, and community. Ready to join us? Apply today.

job_description_lines:
Gilbert Data Analysis Expert Jobs

The Varsity Tutors platform has thousands of students looking for online Data Analysis experts nationally and in Gilbert. As an expert who uses the Varsity Tutors platform, you can earn good money and choose your own schedule while making a fundamental difference in the lives of your students.

Why join our platform?
Enjoy competitive rates and get paid up to 2x per week.Teach as much or as little as you want.Share your knowledge with large groups of students.Instruct online (i.e. “work remotely”) and set your own hours and schedule.We collect payment from the customers, so all you have to do is invoice the session.
What We Look For In a Expert
You have excellent communication skills and a friendly, approachable personality.You can show subject-matter expertise in Data Analysis.You have excellent presentation skills and are comfortable interacting with groups.
Discover all the ways you can reach students through the online platform:
1-on-1 Online Tutoring: connect with an individual student for a highly personalized learning experience.Small Group Classes: meet with small groups (typically 7-9 students) for a more collaborative learning experience.VT+ Classes: teach groups of 25-30 students anything from math fundamentals to video game design.Large Live Classes: share your knowledge with hundreds of students at a time.School@Home: provide support for homeschooling parents with 1-on-1 Online Tutoring and Small Group Classes.Instant Tutoring: accept subject specific, on-demand tutoring sessions whenever you’d like.
About Varsity Tutors And Large Group Instruction

Our mission is to transform the way people learn. We do this by leveraging advanced technology, AI, and the latest in learning science to facilitate a personalized learning experience. Through large group instruction, experts are able to share their knowledge with hundreds of students at a time and facilitate interaction amongst the students. We believe our thoughtful approach to matching students with the right experts can improve outcomes, and we look forward to connecting you with students hungry to learn.

job_description_lines:
Where we work

Ontra’s hybrid workplace allows for employees to choose their own adventure: remote, in-office, or a blend of both!

Available remote locations: United States (CA, CO, CT, FL, GA, IL, MA, MN, NC, NJ, NV, NY, OR, PA, TN, TX, UT, VA, WA), Hong Kong, Singapore, United Kingdom.

Current offices: London, Los Angeles, New York City, San Francisco.

Please note that we currently hire exclusively in the remote and office locations listed above and select jobs may have more specific location requirements.

About the opportunity

The Data Analyst role is a great opportunity for someone who wants to have a direct impact on a growing data organization. You should enjoy getting in the weeds to enhance our teams’ and our products’ data capabilities, acting as an advisor to stakeholders on how to best use data, and want an environment to build upon your analytical skills,

The Data Analyst will help uncover valuable insights and analyses from our legal product data sets to inform decision making. You will have immediate exposure to product and business metrics: how they are defined, evaluated and adopted for driving our business forward. You will work closely with data leadership and product and business stakeholders to perform analyses required to support these metrics. Great communication -- both through the visual presentation of insights and through verbal and written reporting on your work -- is key to success in this role.

The Data Analyst will report directly to the Director of Data and the location is flexible.*

What you’ll do
Become an expert: Build deep understanding of Ontra’s datasets and answer questions using SQL to deliver insights to product and business teamsData visualization: Perform statistical analyses and create informative data visualizations using Redash, Looker, and python libraries to support key product initiativesLong term initiatives: Collaborate with product to develop metrics and dashboards that support company objectives and key results (OKRs)Subject-matter expertise: Provide guidance to stakeholders on how to use data in decision making

What you’ll bring
Data munging and exploration: Experience manipulating data sets and choosing the right data visualizations to inform business decision makingFluency in SQL: can construct complex joins, filters and aggregations to appropriately answer questions of the data and familiarity with querying databasesIntermediate scripting: Experience using a scripting language (python, R, etc.) in analytical work, with a desire to build expertise in pythonEffective communication: Excellent communication and problem solving skills and ability to effectively collaborate with functional leadership across the organizationDetail-oriented mindset: A strong attention to detail and a well-reasoned sense of skepticism toward the results of analyses

Colorado applicants only: The estimated annual cash salary for this role is $140,000. The total compensation package also includes benefits (as further detailed below) as well as unit-based compensation if applicable. Compensation for other locations may vary.*

About Ontra

Ontra, the global leader in Contract Automation and Intelligence, combines AI-enabled software with a global network of highly-trained lawyers to offer a comprehensive solution for recurring legal workflows. By streamlining repetitive legal processes and transforming contracts into structured data, Ontra lowers costs, improves quality, and reduces turnaround times. Ontra is headquartered in San Francisco, with global operations across North America, Europe, and Asia. Learn more at www.ontra.ai.

Our benefits
Competitive salaryOpportunity to participate in one of Ontra’s unit-based compensation programs Medical, dental, and vision insurance base plans at no additional costEmployer-sponsored retirement plansHybrid/remote work flexibility & WFH budget (equivalent of $1K USD)Annual professional development stipend (equivalent of $2K USD)4 months of parental leave (52 weeks for UK employees)Unlimited vacationTwice-weekly lunch perkAnd much more!

Inclusivity

Ontra is committed to the full inclusion of all qualified individuals. As part of this commitment, Ontra will ensure that persons with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodations. If reasonable accommodation is needed to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and/or to receive other benefits and privileges of employment, please contact talent@ontra.ai.
Note on Pay Transparency: Ontra provides an estimate of the compensation for roles that may be hired in Colorado as required by state regulations. Compensation for locations other than Colorado may vary based on (a) location, as Ontra factors in specific location when benchmarking compensation for most roles; (b) individual candidate qualifications; and (c) individual candidate experience. Additionally, Ontra leverages current market data to determine compensation, so posted compensation figures are subject to change as new market data becomes available.

Note on Employment Verification: All employees hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in their particular location.

Note to External Agencies: We are not accepting any blind submissions or resumes/CVs from recruitment agencies. Any candidates sent to Ontra will NOT be accepted or considered as a submission without a signed agreement in place.

Summary

The Data Analyst role is to deliver a final business solution to the operations team through a Power Bi experience. The Data Analyst's technical skills will be put to the test as they shape data into a crispy design through a smooth user experience. Over time the Data Analyst will become a domain expert of supply chains and their use cases. This position will work on cutting edge data technology as a key user on Ryder's Azure Data Lake driving the analytics initiatives. Design critical analytical dashboards, reports and queries to drive strategic business decisions, ad-hoc analysis and identify descriptive and prescriptive solutions for internal Ryder teams and external customers. Dig deep into the core issues of business problems in order to drive a solution that gets at the heart of the causative problem. On this team, the Data Analyst will get the chance to be the expert of supply chain solutions, collaborating with Data Analysts and Scientists, using all the skills in order to exploit data to drive the business forward. This will push the envelope of what is possible within the big data space; streaming live data into a data lake and experimenting with data in the data sandbox.

Essential Functions
Develop Dashboards by understanding business needs, interpret the integrated data and translate this into usable visualizations to drive business decisions, interpreting results and how to utilize the dashboardsEngage the business, evaluating their needs and ad-hoc requests to prioritize product efforts creating new innovative solutionsKnowledge of the Ryder Business, understanding the complexity of the supply chain world and the role that data has within this ecosystemEnhance data maturity and integration to standardize the core value add functionality enabling a multiplier effect
Additional Responsibilities
Performs other duties as assigned.
Skills And Abilities
Experience developing BI solutions with tools like: Power BI TableauExposure using tools like: ETL tools (Alteryx or SSIS) Data manipulation tools (SQL) Object oriented development stacks (.net) (preferred)Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to express complex technical concepts in business termsSupport product innovation, working closely with technology throughout the build, test, and release of the product using agile methodologies
Qualifications
Bachelor's degree required Supply Chain, Data Analytics or equivalentMaster's degree preferred Supply Chain, Data Analytics, MBA or equivalentTwo (2) years or more Applied Project(s) Experience: Experience in demonstrating, digital transformation, data management in an educational/project or intern type environment requiredTwo (2) years or more 2-4 years experience in creating dashboards for diagnostic analysis across the business. Experience working in a cloud environment a plus. preferred
DOT Regulated: No

Job Category: Data Science & Analytics

About Us 
Motionworks is the trusted population intelligence expert that empowers customers with privacy-compliant, innovative data solutions to help them make smarter, more confident decisions. Motionworks is the fusion of three powerhouse companies in the mobility space, Intermx, Transport Foundry, and Standard Data with a client portfolio that spans advertising, government planning, tourism, transportation engineering, and retail. Powered by geospatial technology and exceptional data scientists, engineers, and UX experts, Motionworks delivers a wide range of high-value mobility insights that provide historical, real-time, normative, and predictive intelligence about how people move around the globe. 
Job Summary 
As a fast-growing startup, Motionworks is looking for strong candidates at the intersection of data engineering and data science with demonstrated interest in urban planning or public policy. We want people with a passion for data modeling, software development, and applying your trade to make the world a better place. You will be tasked with: Designing, prototyping, and developing innovative data solutions for geospatial problems Analyzing transportation data patterns to ensure our products accurately reflect current conditions Building mathematical/machine learning models that sit on top of our primary products Developing and managing large scale data repositories and data lakes for our supply chain pipeline Collaborate with our partners and clients performing consulting work to address their data/product needs Collaborate with other internal or external developers, engineers, and scientists on new methodologies. Improving, validating, documenting, and performing analytics work on our current data solutions 
An ideal candidate for this position must be a solid developer who thinks about the physical world in which people move. These attributes are combined to critically analyze a problem at hand, do research on viable and effective solutions, perform modeling work, implement solutions, and analytically assess the results. You will need to communicate complex concepts and solutions to technical and nontechnical audiences through effective visualizations, statistical analysis, and documentation. 
We would want you to be organized yet scrappy, thoughtful, and most importantly, have a strong desire to learn. 
Required Qualifications and Skills 
Masters in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, analytical City Planning, or Geography (or equivalent degree) or Bachelors in similar with 2+ years of experience in quantitative analytics, data science, or data engineering. Demonstrated development in Python Understanding of cloud computing (preferably AWS and GCP) Demonstrated SQL experience in at least one of the following: PostgreSQL, PostGIS, BigQuery, RedShift, or Snowflake Proven experience working with geospatial data (e.g., geojson, shapefiles) Experience with version control (preferably Git/GitHub) Experience with Linux/Unix command line Ability to build/test statistical and/or machine learning model Ability to create effective visualizations in at least one of the following: Tableau, Matplotlib, or ggplot2 Solid critical thinking and problem-solving skills 
Preferred Qualifications and Skills Experience building data pipelines and automating processes with Apache Airflow Experience with Docker containers Transportation modeling consulting or public sector service 
Location San Diego, California, or Remote with occasional travel 
Benefits Medical, dental, and vision coverage for you and your dependents First year of employment gives two weeks of PTO, four weeks thereafter 14 holidays and flex holidays 401(k) plan Employee equity

Mesa Data Analysis Expert Jobs

The Varsity Tutors platform has thousands of students looking for online Data Analysis experts nationally and in Mesa. As an expert who uses the Varsity Tutors platform, you can earn good money and choose your own schedule while making a fundamental difference in the lives of your students.

Why join our platform?
Enjoy competitive rates and get paid up to 2x per week.Teach as much or as little as you want.Share your knowledge with large groups of students.Instruct online (i.e. “work remotely”) and set your own hours and schedule.We collect payment from the customers, so all you have to do is invoice the session.
What We Look For In a Expert
You have excellent communication skills and a friendly, approachable personality.You can show subject-matter expertise in Data Analysis.You have excellent presentation skills and are comfortable interacting with groups.
Discover all the ways you can reach students through the online platform:
1-on-1 Online Tutoring: connect with an individual student for a highly personalized learning experience.Small Group Classes: meet with small groups (typically 7-9 students) for a more collaborative learning experience.VT+ Classes: teach groups of 25-30 students anything from math fundamentals to video game design.Large Live Classes: share your knowledge with hundreds of students at a time.School@Home: provide support for homeschooling parents with 1-on-1 Online Tutoring and Small Group Classes.Instant Tutoring: accept subject specific, on-demand tutoring sessions whenever you’d like.
About Varsity Tutors And Large Group Instruction

Our mission is to transform the way people learn. We do this by leveraging advanced technology, AI, and the latest in learning science to facilitate a personalized learning experience. Through large group instruction, experts are able to share their knowledge with hundreds of students at a time and facilitate interaction amongst the students. We believe our thoughtful approach to matching students with the right experts can improve outcomes, and we look forward to connecting you with students hungry to learn.

To solve climate change, wealth inequality, supply chain stability, and national security we must change how our global supply chains work. Altana is a Trusted Commerce Platform built on a shared source of truth for the global supply chain. The purpose of Altana is to enable resilient, sustainable, secure, and inclusive global commerce: Globalization 2.0.

We have built a layer of shared intelligence across the world’s supply chain information: a living map of trillions of dollars of B2B commercial activity, covering 400M companies connected by billions of shipments. This knowledge graph powers Altana’s Trusted Commerce Platform - the Altana Atlas - which, after only three years since founding, is already used by many of the world’s most important governments, enterprises, and logistics providers.

Our product suite enables our customers to gain unprecedented visibility, benefit from shared artificial intelligence across a federated network of data, and interact across the network through a shared source of truth. We help our customers to build and manage trusted global supply chains.

About The Job

The Data Operations organization is a critical support organization to various data science and engineering teams at Altana AI. As a team we provide infrastructure for human insights into DS and AI initiatives that are core to Altana’s product. Data Operations partners closely with our product teams to come up with innovative ways to further enrich and collect data to increase Altana’s data coverage.

As a data analyst in the data operations team, you are responsible for architecting and managing data labeling and annotation workflows end-to-end while actively working with different internal stakeholders to assess training data needs and delivery insides into algorithmic performance while continuously enhancing data driven processes internally as well as externally with our annotation vendors.

As an ideal candidate you are a strong communicator, technically curious, love documentation and processes while keeping them flexible to meet changing engineering needs.

Responsibilities
Scoping and managing of multiple annotation workflows in parallel Definition and ownership of project success metricsAbility to work cross functionally to identify needs for human annotated dataDay-to-day management of vendor team responsible for data labeling effortsIdentify opportunities to improve efficiency in labeling processes through process improvements and/or annotation tool improvements
Requirements
Experience in a Data Annotation, Data Operations, Project Management, Vendor Management or Sales Engineering role within a data driven organizationAbility to operate in an unstructured research environmentStrong verbal and written communication abilitiesCommitment to an inclusive corporate cultureBaseline familiarity with technical platforms, databases, or statistical software Familiarity with or a desire to learn about machine learning models
Nice To Have
Worked in a remote environment Comfortable in using Python for data analyticsForeign language skills
Salary Range: $50,000-135,000

Why it’s great to work at Altana
We love to collaborate, and we win as a team!We are committed to engineering excellenceWe value personal and professional developmentWe learn from diverse backgrounds and perspectivesWe impact the world, from enabling developing countries to identifying drug traffickers
Altana is an equal opportunity employer with a commitment to inclusion across race and ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, age, religion, physical ability, veteran status, and national origin. We offer a comprehensive healthcare package and paid parental leave of 3 months for the primary caregiver and 1 month for the secondary caregiver.

Overview

Frontdoor is a company that’s obsessed with taking the hassle out of owning a home. With services powered by people and enabled by technology, it is the parent company of four home service plan brands: American Home Shield, HSA, Landmark and OneGuard, as well as ProConnect, an on-demand membership service for home repairs and maintenance, and Streem, a technology company that enables businesses to serve customers through an enhanced augmented reality, computer vision and machine learning platform. Frontdoor serves 2.2 million customers across the U.S. through a network of approximately 17,000 pre-qualified contractor firms that employ an estimated 60,000 technicians. The company’s customizable home service plans help customers protect and maintain their homes from costly and unexpected breakdowns of essential home systems and appliances. With 50 years of home services experience, the company responds to over four million service requests annually. For details, visit frontdoorhome.com.

Responsibilities

Responsible for providing data analysis to recommend actions of a moderately complex nature to improve business processes to management.
Gather, validate, and analyze data, to successfully manage internal performance reporting and messaging for OperationsAnalyze lost productivity within our BPO vendors and estimate budgetary impactsCompile and analyze interval call volume data and lost productivity risks and make short term schedule recommendations to create operational efficienciesOwn agent performance scorecards, published monthly, to assist management with performance managementTrack overtime from a productive and budgetary perspective and forecast expected monthly expense and requirementsPresent weekly staffing changes and assist in determining staffing needs to meet operational goalsAssist with labor requirement forecasting and make recommendations on the timing of staff additions based on historical behaviorsPerform frequent ad hoc reporting on demand to assist Operations management with decision making
Qualifications
3 years overall data analysis experience with proven experience in SQL, R, PowerBI, Looker or other data management/visualization tools.Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, or similar field.Ability to mine data, compile and manipulate in multiple systems/programs and analyze resultsSQL (Snowflake)RLookerPowerBIPythonAbility to create effective presentations for management.Excellent communication skills

Job Description:Phreesia is looking for a Data Analyst who is passionate about healthcare and solving complex problems with data to join our Life Sciences team. This multi-faceted position will conduct data analysis and data validation to tell a story that disseminates key insights to drive the business.  Does this sound like you?  
Experienced with healthcare data and strong analytic and quantitative skills Thrive in a collaborative, fast-paced and challenging environment Enjoy working with multiple data sources and write SQL queries to extract the data, use tools like Python to gain efficiencies, and tools like Excel or Tableau to organize, sort and summarize the data 
What You'll Do: 
Learn and understand Phreesia’s data landscape, leveraging that knowledge to answer questions, solve problems and improve processes Conduct both ad-hoc analysis for cross-departmental requests as well as develop and maintain ongoing reporting for numerous internal initiatives Analyze and interpret data, producing clear and compelling reports for different audiences, communicating recommendations to various levels of management Leverage SQL and Excel to organize and aggregate data and summarize for reporting, handling large and complex datasets in different formats and identifying opportunities for data product improvements Trace through and perform quality assurance on queries and find efficiencies in coding using tools such as Python, Jupiter Notebooks Collaborate with team members and leadership to proactively identify business patterns through quantitative data analysis 
What You'll Bring: 
BSc/BA in Health Informatics, Public Health, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or related discipline 2+ years of healthcare experience in data or business analysis Detail oriented with strong problem solving and analytical skills Strong SQL skills, and experience with Python and data visualization tools (i.e Tableau, Qlikview, Power BI) Ability to reconcile and analyze large data sets to extract key metrics and identify trends Strong interpersonal skills, including the ability to work in a cross-functional environment 
Nice to Have: 
Experience with R 
Who We Are:At Phreesia, we’re looking for smart and passionate people to help drive our mission of creating a better, more engaging healthcare experience. We’re committed to helping healthcare organizations succeed in an ever-evolving landscape by transforming the way healthcare is delivered. Our SaaS platform digitizes appointment check-in and offers tools to engage patients, improve efficiency, optimize staffing, and enhance clinical care.Phreesia cares about our employees by providing a diverse and dynamic work environment. We’re a five-time winner of Modern Healthcare Magazine’s Best Places to Work in Healthcare award and we’ve been recognized on the Bloomberg Gender Equality Index. We are dedicated to continuously improving our employee experience by launching new programs and initiatives. If you thrive in a culture of recognition, value inclusivity, professional development, and growth opportunities, Phreesia could be a great fit!
 Top-rated Employee Benefits:
100% Remote work + home office expense reimbursementsCompetitive compensation + equity grants for all employeesUnlimited PTO + 8 company holidaysMonthly allowance for cell phone + internet + wellness100% Paid 12-week parental leave to our U.S. employees, as well as a generous parental benefit to our employees in CanadaVariety of insurance coverage for people (and pets!)Continuing education and professional certification reimbursementWe strive to provide a diverse and inclusive environment and are an equal opportunity employer.

Data Analyst Research & Planning Consultants, LP, has an immediate opening for an experienced data analyst. This person will analyze data, prepare presentations, and write narrative analyses in expert reports for use in commercial litigation, personal injury litigation, and regulatory proceedings. This is a full-time, salaried position with benefits. We pay competitive salaries with a potential annual bonus based on the performance of the consultant and the firm. RPC offers a full benefit package including paid leave, health insurance, 401(k) plan, health savings account, and flexible spending account. RPC is an equal opportunity employer. Duties of the position include:data analysis in Excel and SQLpreparing written reports explaining data sources and methods of analysisconstruction of efficient queries to manipulate large amounts of dataloading, cleaning, and management of data in Microsoft SQL Serveradministering the Health Data Store Qualifications:Bachelor’s degree in business, computer science, mathematics, economics, or statistics.Strong quantitative skills.3-5 years of post-degree experience in data analysis using Microsoft SQL and EXCEL.Read, write, and speak fluent English.Experience using advanced EXCEL functions.Experience analyzing medical claims data and Medicare Cost Report data a plus.Experience using STATA and ArcGIS a plus. Location: The RPC office is in Austin, Texas. If the candidate is in the Austin area, they will be expected to work in the office. If working remotely, candidate must have the ability to work from home in a quiet space and access to high-speed internet. RPC will provide the computer and accessory equipment necessary. The job is full-time (40 – 50 hours per week) and because of internal and project deadlines additional hours will be required occasionally.
About RPC: Research & Planning Consultants, LP, is based in Austin, Texas, and was founded in 1972. RPC prepares economic, statistical and financial reports used in litigation and regulatory proceedings for a national clientele. The firm has special expertise in the health care industry but works with a wide range of industries. See our web site: www.rpcconsulting.com for more about the firm. To Apply: Send a current resume or Curriculum vitae with a cover letter describing your education and work experience. Please indicate in the email your current address and phone number. Salary: $75,000-90,000 based on experience

Dice is the leading career destination for tech experts at every stage of their careers. Our client, Prudent Technologies and Consulting, is seeking the following. Apply via Dice today!

An excellent long term W2 Contract opportunity (100% Remote) for a Data Quality Analyst with our direct client in San Jose, CA

Job Title: Data Quality Analyst (100% Remote)

6 + Months Contract position/Candidates must be willing to work on W2 Basis

Rate : $50/hr to $60/hr

Requirements

Undergraduate degree in Finance, Statistics, Information Technologies, or related field

5 years of experience working within data quality for business operations

Minimum 2 years of experience, data profiling, data quality at an enterprise level

Prior experience working in or with finance operations teams & systems, SAP S4HANA (OTC/BRIM), Revpro & Anaplan.

Salesforce is a plus

Experience working with SAP BODS/Information Steward, Snowflake, Tableau, or similar tools Ability to engage, communicate & challenge effectively with management to provide clear, concise explanations of data quality issues and their business impact to gain support for the resolution Ability to communicate data quality practices and concepts as needed to educate and engage stakeholders

Develop reports to effectively identify data issues, root causes, and business impacts

Experience with automation of data quality cleansing & enrichment services, preferably with SAP Data Services, using both internal and external data sources Experience translating business data needs into technical language and partnering with IT teams to ensure effective QA / UAT of solution delivery.

Experience working with offshore development teams to scope, prioritize & manage work delivery pipelines & backlogs Prior exposure to finance regulations such as SOX, and data regulations such as GDPR, CCPA Work effectively within an agile environment, using tools like JIRA, ServiceNow & confluence to prioritize, document, and deliver data-related services.

Required Skills

BUSINESS OPERATIONS, DATA PROFILING, DATA QUALITY, DATA SERVICES, DATA SOURCES

job_description_lines:
About Academic AnalyticsAcademic Analytics is a full-service provider of business intelligence solutions for higher education. Academic Analytics’ tools and solutions support university leaders as they strive for excellence in their research enterprise. Our data inform these leaders to better understand strengths and opportunities, establish standards and benchmarks, allocate resources, and cultivate faculty development. Our products continually evolve to meet the needs of our clients, often based on feedback from the university research community. The Data Analyst will assist in the development, implementation, and maintenance of complex queries, reports, and analyses related to research universities. Reporting to the Analytics Manager, you will provide expertise and insight to engage and stimulate increased client utilization of Academic Analytics solutions as strategic assets in client decision making and program assessment. You will work with a team of data analysts as part of a dynamic client service operation. This is a remote position. We are looking for candidates on the East Coast and in the Midwest. The candidate must live and be authorized to work in the United States. Applicants must submit cover letter and resume for consideration. 
What You'll Do HerePerform data analysis to support client objectives, turning data into insights that drive business decisions.Define and scope report requirements (in collaboration with clients), design and develop report-oriented code (either in SAS or SQL); build, test, and standardize reports, data visualizations, and dashboards (either in Tableau or Excel).Ensure data quality and integrity by participating in database QA and client report peer review process.Identify and prepare data content for webinars and public communications and presentations; collaborate with clients to define the scope of new analyses and present completed reports to client stakeholders.In collaboration with Client Solutions Team, partner with individual client institutions to tailor the implementation of Academic Analytics products and solutions to each client’s unique needs.Desired Experience and Skills:Bachelor’s Degree3-5 years data analysis experience or academic trainingExcellent written and oral communication skillsStrong critical thinking skills and a solutions-oriented, innovative approach to exploring dataExtensive knowledge of SQL and/or SAS requiredExtensive knowledge of Tableau Desktop requiredWorking knowledge of Tableau Server requiredWorking knowledge of Microsoft Office suite of tools (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) and videoconference software (Zoom, Microsoft Teams)Understanding of basic statistics and research methodsExperience working in higher education and/or institutional research a plusAbility to develop strong, collaborative working relationships with colleagues in a virtual work environment· Needs to be flexible with willingness to adapt to changesExcellent organizational skills and flexibility to handle several projects simultaneously, prioritizing tasks and meeting deadlinesAbility to operate in high volume work environmentProactive work style: will take initiative to make personal connections with key personnel internally and externally, take ownership of projects and see through to completion.Ability to interact professionally with a diverse group of data users from various functional levelsAbility to think analytically and communicate statistical concepts and research findings to expert and non-expert users
Work EnvironmentOperate in a virtual structure with employees working from home. This role routinely uses standard office equipment such as computers, phones, photocopiers.Travel estimated at 10%

Overview

The Data Analyst is responsible for data gathering, analysis, and reporting. An individual in this role will work directly with data and information, creating meaningful analyses, reports, and management presentations in support of business unit or function activities and performance. This role will be required to translate business needs into data and analytical requirements and deliver those requirements within deadlines and at a high level of accuracy.

Responsibilities

Principal Accountabilities & Deliverables
Collects and analyzes complex data for reporting and/or performance (trend) analysisDevelops and utilizes complex SQL queries and other data extraction techniques to prepare data for analysis, ensuring alignment between the data and the underlying business processes that the data reflects.Prepares a wide variety of reports and provides data and management information for internal audiencesParticipates in high-level business initiatives and assist with all levels of metric reporting Report Automation- work with IT to publish canned reports based on business needs/requests.Performs the analysis, explores all appropriate options and performs constant validation against existing data/reporting.Serves as data steward to validate high profile or external data to ensure accurate reporting.Other duties as assigned.
Qualifications

Knowledge, Skills, & Abilities

Education / Experience
Bachelor’s Degree required in Economics, Math, Computer Science or related field2+ years’ experience in data gathering, data organization, and analysis required
Skills
Intermediate to Advanced SQL querying skills requiredAdvanced working knowledge of Microsoft ExcelBusiness Objects/Business Intelligence experience preferredStrong knowledge and experience with relational database platforms, including SQL ServerExcellent written and oral communication skills, especially in conveying technical concepts to non-technical audiencesComfortable working in a fast-paced environment where deadlines are essentialCompetent in organizing, planning, and prioritizing workStrong attention to detail to ensure accuracy and provide validation of resultsStrong analytical skills and ability to identify appropriate analytical approaches depending on the business need.

Summary

The Data Analyst role is to deliver a final business solution to the operations team through a Power Bi experience. The Data Analyst's technical skills will be put to the test as they shape data into a crispy design through a smooth user experience. Over time the Data Analyst will become a domain expert of supply chains and their use cases. This position will work on cutting edge data technology as a key user on Ryder's Azure Data Lake driving the analytics initiatives. Design critical analytical dashboards, reports and queries to drive strategic business decisions, ad-hoc analysis and identify descriptive and prescriptive solutions for internal Ryder teams and external customers. Dig deep into the core issues of business problems in order to drive a solution that gets at the heart of the causative problem. On this team, the Data Analyst will get the chance to be the expert of supply chain solutions, collaborating with Data Analysts and Scientists, using all the skills in order to exploit data to drive the business forward. This will push the envelope of what is possible within the big data space; streaming live data into a data lake and experimenting with data in the data sandbox.

Essential Functions
Develop Dashboards by understanding business needs, interpret the integrated data and translate this into usable visualizations to drive business decisions, interpreting results and how to utilize the dashboardsEngage the business, evaluating their needs and ad-hoc requests to prioritize product efforts creating new innovative solutionsKnowledge of the Ryder Business, understanding the complexity of the supply chain world and the role that data has within this ecosystemEnhance data maturity and integration to standardize the core value add functionality enabling a multiplier effect
Additional Responsibilities
Performs other duties as assigned.
Skills And Abilities
Experience developing BI solutions with tools like: Power BI TableauExposure using tools like: ETL tools (Alteryx or SSIS) Data manipulation tools (SQL) Object oriented development stacks (.net) (preferred)Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to express complex technical concepts in business termsSupport product innovation, working closely with technology throughout the build, test, and release of the product using agile methodologies
Qualifications
Bachelor's degree required Supply Chain, Data Analytics or equivalentMaster's degree preferred Supply Chain, Data Analytics, MBA or equivalentTwo (2) years or more Applied Project(s) Experience: Experience in demonstrating, digital transformation, data management in an educational/project or intern type environment requiredTwo (2) years or more 2-4 years experience in creating dashboards for diagnostic analysis across the business. Experience working in a cloud environment a plus. preferred
DOT Regulated: No

job_description_lines:
Job Description:Phreesia is looking for a Data Analyst who is passionate about healthcare and solving complex problems with data to join our Life Sciences team. This multi-faceted position will conduct data analysis and data validation to tell a story that disseminates key insights to drive the business.  Does this sound like you?  
Experienced with healthcare data and strong analytic and quantitative skills Thrive in a collaborative, fast-paced and challenging environment Enjoy working with multiple data sources and write SQL queries to extract the data, use tools like Python to gain efficiencies, and tools like Excel or Tableau to organize, sort and summarize the data 
What You'll Do: 
Learn and understand Phreesia’s data landscape, leveraging that knowledge to answer questions, solve problems and improve processes Conduct both ad-hoc analysis for cross-departmental requests as well as develop and maintain ongoing reporting for numerous internal initiatives Analyze and interpret data, producing clear and compelling reports for different audiences, communicating recommendations to various levels of management Leverage SQL and Excel to organize and aggregate data and summarize for reporting, handling large and complex datasets in different formats and identifying opportunities for data product improvements Trace through and perform quality assurance on queries and find efficiencies in coding using tools such as Python, Jupiter Notebooks Collaborate with team members and leadership to proactively identify business patterns through quantitative data analysis 
What You'll Bring: 
BSc/BA in Health Informatics, Public Health, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or related discipline 2+ years of healthcare experience in data or business analysis Detail oriented with strong problem solving and analytical skills Strong SQL skills, and experience with Python and data visualization tools (i.e Tableau, Qlikview, Power BI) Ability to reconcile and analyze large data sets to extract key metrics and identify trends Strong interpersonal skills, including the ability to work in a cross-functional environment 
Nice to Have: 
Experience with R 
Who We Are:At Phreesia, we’re looking for smart and passionate people to help drive our mission of creating a better, more engaging healthcare experience. We’re committed to helping healthcare organizations succeed in an ever-evolving landscape by transforming the way healthcare is delivered. Our SaaS platform digitizes appointment check-in and offers tools to engage patients, improve efficiency, optimize staffing, and enhance clinical care.Phreesia cares about our employees by providing a diverse and dynamic work environment. We’re a five-time winner of Modern Healthcare Magazine’s Best Places to Work in Healthcare award and we’ve been recognized on the Bloomberg Gender Equality Index. We are dedicated to continuously improving our employee experience by launching new programs and initiatives. If you thrive in a culture of recognition, value inclusivity, professional development, and growth opportunities, Phreesia could be a great fit!
 Top-rated Employee Benefits:
100% Remote work + home office expense reimbursementsCompetitive compensation + equity grants for all employeesUnlimited PTO + 8 company holidaysMonthly allowance for cell phone + internet + wellness100% Paid 12-week parental leave to our U.S. employees, as well as a generous parental benefit to our employees in CanadaVariety of insurance coverage for people (and pets!)Continuing education and professional certification reimbursementWe strive to provide a diverse and inclusive environment and are an equal opportunity employer.

job_description_lines:
MAPP Advisors is looking for an ambitious, self-starter to join our team as a Data Analyst. This is a unique opportunity to gain invaluable experience working directly with senior management to build out MAPP’s Portfolio Optimization division. This division analyzes big data sets and tracks complex money movement to identify revenue opportunities and cost savings for clients. The engagements also involve consulting services such as implementing strategic revenue initiatives, vendor selection and contract negotiations, and compliance reviews.
You will gain a deep understanding of the fintech industry, the largest investment sector in the world for the last three years. The position reports to the Head of our Portfolio Optimization Division who is based in Raleigh, North Carolina. Remote applicants are accepted, with the ability to travel to meet with team members and clients. 

ResponsibilitiesAssist with client communication and project management, including document collection, review, and organizationIngest, review, and sanitize data to buildout and maintain multiple data sets for analysis and reportingIdentify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data setsDevelop clear visualizations to convey complicated data in a straightforward fashionReview internal processes to identify and implement new analyses techniques, operational efficiencies, and process automation to contribute to the improvement of existing processes
QualificationsBachelor's or Master's degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Accounting, Computer Science or equivalent experienceIdeally 1 - 2 years' Data Analysis experienceAdvanced experience with Microsoft Office product suite, Adobe Pro, and statistical packages for analyzing datasets (Excel, VBA, SQL, SPSS, SAS)Experience with data models, database design, data mining, and segmentation techniquesA curious mind that loves to solve problemsHardworking and dedicated, with ability to take direction and absorb information quicklyStrong analytical skills with the ability to manage significant amounts of information with attention to detailAbility to manage multiple projects within tight timeframes

About UsMetLife Legal Plans is the leading consumer legal service in the United States, providing the best legal services for working families. Through our network of over 17,000 attorneys, members of our legal insurance plans can resolve legal matters that range from buying a new home to adopting a child. You can learn more at legalplans.com.
Whether you are making a will after starting a family, negotiating the contract on your dream home, or just want the peace of mind of having our attorneys on your side, we make it easy and affordable to get quality legal help.
About the roleAt MetLife Legal Plans, we build technology that makes it easy to solve legal problems. With millions of customers, we rely on data-driven decision making to improve our business. We are looking for a junior data scientist to join our team and help us organize and analyze all of our data.
This role reports to the Director of Data Science. Duties include modeling, report generation, investigative work, building analytics infrastructure, business process optimization, product development, and data security. You should be familiar with hunting for answers to complex business questions and running experiments to gather additional data when necessary. You should be equally at home designing, developing, and maintaining customized reports using Tableau.
You will work on a nimble, distributed team that is passionate about producing insights that drive real business impact. Our technology is evolving rapidly, so you should be comfortable working in a fast-paced, unstructured environment.
MetLife Legal Plans is headquartered in Cleveland, Ohio, but our technology team is remote by default, so you can work from anywhere in the United States.
 Relevant SkillsDemonstrated experience in Tableau or similar tools.Experience designing effective visualizations.Proficiency in SQL and relational database modeling fundamentals.Knowledge of analytical tools such as SAS, R, Matlab, or STATA and scripting languages such as Python and Perl.Strong oral and written communication skills, with the ability to effectively communicate with both technical and non-technical audiences at all levels.

job_description_lines: We invite you to explore a future with us at PRA Group, a diverse and growing company that has a tangible impact on the global economy. Position Summary: We're based in Norfolk, VA... but you don't need to be... This Data Analyst role will work in the area of Strategy, charged with maintaining and troubleshooting SQL coding processes for the purpose of managing segmentation criteria for US Core Operation channels. This role is focused on querying and analyzing the business performance to facilitate improvement to the segmentation criteria, processes, and activity decisions being taken. This role is expected to assist with the management of account inventory, collection activity, and customer data by maintaining operational activity segmentation selection (SQL based) processes and their required monitoring and controls for quality assurance. The Analyst role will be responsible for building ad-hoc queries to conduct intermediate level analysis to measure the impact of strategy improvements and provide recommendations for strategy testing and criteria adjustments. Professional Experience/Qualifications: Bachelor’s Degree required A minimum of 2-4 years of professional analyst related experience and/or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience preferred Strong skills such as ability to create complex queries such as Joins. Left joins, Pivots, etc. Ability to write SQL code for intermediate query level functioning including the ability to: Import data into SQL Server from various sources (text files, spreadsheets, Access DBs) Export data out of SQL Server to various targets (text files, spreadsheets, DBs) Execute existing T-SQL Queries and Scripts; Modify T-SQL Queries and Scripts; Create T-SQL Queries and Scripts; Data Mining/Preparation Skills Analytical problem-solving skills Ability to complete basic business problem solving task assigned Ability to interpret data, identify trends, and report data findings Intermediate level of analytics autonomy and independence. Project implementation focus. Capable of project day to day oversight on task needed to execute. Must have effective organizational, time-management and high attention to detail skills. Strong data analysis capability with technical knowledge Ability to mine, clean, and manage large data sets and troubleshoot data issues identified Knowledge of data preparation methods: handling of missing data and general imputation Strong excel skills (charts/graphs/formulas/macros) Key Responsibilities (other duties may be assigned Data analysis & reporting using Oracle SQL, MS SQL, and other statistical tools Execution and troubleshooting of SQL Stored Procedure processes Conduct analysis to identify the impact of process changes in areas of opportunity for segmentation improvements and process changes. Enhance the monitoring and control mechanisms to strategy owned processes to ensure we maintain compliance with policies and procedures. Maintain Policy and Procedure documentation along with change management and testing documentation as required. Dig into data and raw information through statistical analysis to discover trends and patterns that can be used to extract valuable business insights Participate in ad-hoc analyst tasks in addition to day to day process execution tasks. Maintain and oversee the performance of champion / challenger testing processes as it relates to existing activities or other alternative strategies being developed. Build and maintain Power BI dashboards for showing activity performance as it relates to strategy processes being maintained by the department. Identify issues and process improvement opportunities and work with other areas of the business to analysis, report and resolve discrepancies (including taking ownership of actions/projects where appropriate) Partner with compliance to ensure processes are aligned with regulatory and risk mitigation criteria. Identifying and capitalizing on improvement opportunities. At PRA Group, we're committed to helping our employees reach their highest potential by offering competitive salaries, proprietary training programs, tuition reimbursement programs, comprehensive healthcare, dental and vision benefits, maternal and paternal leave, holiday pay and PTO, an employee assistance program, and valuable opportunities to establish a long career within our organization. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment regardless of age, race, color, sex, gender, religion, national origin, physical or mental disability, citizenship, or any other classes recognized by state or local law or any other characteristic protected under applicable federal, state or local law. We are a drug free workplace.
